videos.title: Math Antics - Convert any Fraction to a Decimal
videos.description:
http://www.mathantics.com

Here is the video mentioned about converting Base-10 fractions: http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=_jcW-ZgpRbM
Here is the video mentioned about decimal numbers: http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=Mst8iZjIpFE
And here is the video mentioned about comparing fractions: http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=KNdUJQ_qd4U

Here we learn that you can use division to convert any fraction into its decimal form. The video clearly illustrates the 'long division' algorithm and also teaches the notation for expressing repeating decimal answers.

Math Antics is a web site featuring free math videos and more!

videos.title: Math Antics - Basic Probability
videos.description:
This is a re-upload to correct some terminology.
In the previous version we suggested that the terms “odds” and “probability” could be used interchangeably.  While this may be okay in casual conversation (since both have to do with the likelihood of an event), the two terms mean something slightly different in math and are calculated differently.  We apologize for any confusion.
